		<div class="title">Re: FTL</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">It *really is* like NetHack - every game is randomized, and you might be struggling for fuel, one playthrough, only to have a surplus of fuel, scrap, and crew the next time - but only crappy weapons!<br />
<br />
And, like the Wizard of Yendor, the &quot;end game&quot; is always the same encounter, but the context of that encounter depends entirely on your playthrough: what enhancements you have, your crew's expertise, the condition of your ship, etc.<br />
<br />
After a dozen playthroughs, I've tried a variety of offensive and defensive approaches, as well as exploratory and streamlined exploration. There are a lot of variables here :) I would not call this game shallow. Randomized for multiple re-experiencings, sure, but not shallow! :)</blockquote>
	</div>
