<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">
<div style="display: none;">
<br />
So, I started up on the 3rd try.  Was rationing my missiles, managed to pick up a Transporter early on.  but then lost 1 of my crewmen in a random action (damned spiders).  So, two rockmen, My tactics actually became abandoning the Bulwark in favor of boarding.  Then I found a Firebomb.  Things became easy.  And I started picking up crew, better weapons blah blah blah, life is good.  <br />
<br />
Final weapons were 2 Ion Blast 2's, Pike Beam, Firebomb(had enough power to run both Ion's &amp; either beam or Bomb).  Anti-Ship Drone 1, Defense Drone 2, &amp; Hull repair drone 2 that I swapped in between combats.  <br />
<br />
basic tactics:  Both Ion's open fire on weapons (once shields are down and weapons locked down switch one to other system Shields usually) - If Medbay firebomb it -- Beam in 2 Rockman boarding team.  If no medbay firebomb some other 2 slot room like the Bridge.  Very rarely did I have to pull out my Rockmen due to low health.  and when I did their guys started running scared &amp; the fires ran rampant.<br />
<br />
On the boss - both Ion blasts went to autofireing 1 on Engine, 1 on Cloak.  Rockmen beamed into the Missile weapon for boarding action.  Then the Ion, then the Heavy laser.  at that Point I Firebombed the medbay - beamed my 2 rockmen in.  Interestingly, they left me alone -So  I firebombed the cloak, That got their attention.   worked my way through the blast doors.  took out door controls, and started killing their guys.  (did have to evac once to heal).  Left the guy manning the Beam weapon alive (per spoiler - crew carries from phase to phase.).  Easiest phase 1 I've ever done.  Shut down the Firebomb and sliced &amp; Diced with the Pike Beam.<br />
<br />
<br />
Phase 2:  My boarders went directly to the drone bay - Ion weapons went to rapid fire against The missiles &amp; lasers. Their boarding drone landed in my weapons bay being manned by a Mantis &amp; Engi.   After the drone bay was knocked out got my boarding crew out, Pike beam fired up, along with Anti-Ship drone.  I did have to activate the Hull Repair drone during the Power Surge.  (did not manage to find a cloak for sale when I had the scrap to buy it).<br />
<br />
Phase 3:  Nothing to it.  No crew left onboard the flagship - Boarded to take out the weapons, Ion's fireing against the shields, Pike beam sliced em, anti-ship drone fired away.  <br />
<br />
Go FEDERATION!   
</div>
