	</div>
	
	
		<div class="title">Re: FTL</div>
	
	<div class="content">
		<blockquote class="restore">I got crazy lucky on one playthrough and unlocked both the stealth ship and another. The stealth ship is *not* easy to use. The weapons are weak, and no shields, but it does start with cloaking ability. You can buy shields, but it's expensive - 150 scrap. The layout of the ship is rather nice, for what that's worth.<br />
<br />
I've used the Bulwark a few times, and it's definitely built to be a &quot;tank&quot; as opposed to a nimble fighter. I stacked mine with all the missile weapons I could find, ignored shields on the opposition, and scavenged for missiles whenever I could. It worked out well, but, of course, I was destroyed by the end boss ;)<br />
<br />
Most of my games aren't built to get to the end-game and beat the boss. Not yet, at least - I'm still exploring various combinations of the game. I fear that once I figure out a technique to win, I'll build all my ships to do that, and most of the fun will be sucked out. I still like the randomness of what you can find in the sectors (a la Nethack).</blockquote>
	</div>
